0Kambli%20scored%201084%20runs%20in%20his%2017-Test%20career%20at%20an%20impressive%20average%20of%2054.20%2C%20which%20included%20four%20centuries%20and%20three%20fifties.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20SPORTS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20Mosque%20And%204%20Shops%3A%20Ex%20Pak%20PM%20Liaquat%20Ali%20Khan%20At%20Centre%20Of%20UP%20Land%20Row%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20western%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20district%20of%20Muzaffarnagar%20is%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20a%20property%20dispute%20that%20stretches%20back%20to%20the%20tumultuous%20years%20of%20the%20Partition.%20The%20property%20in%20question%2C%20a%20mosque%20and%20four%20shops%20located%20near%20the%20Muzaffarnagar%20railway%20station%20has%20recently%20been%20declared%20%26quot%3Benemy%20property%26quot%3B%20following%20an%20investigation.%20The%20ownership%20of%20the%20land%20traces%20its%20roots%20to%20the%20family%20of%20Pakistan's%20first%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Liaquat%20Ali%20Khan%2C%20with%20claims%20that%20it%20was%20illegally%20occupied%20after%20the%20Partition%20in%201947.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20dispute%20has%20triggered%20debates%20over%20the%20legitimacy%20of%20its%20ownership%2C%20with%20one%20faction%20claiming%20the%20land%20belongs%20to%20the%20Waqf%20Board%2C%20while%20another%20argues%20it%20is%20a%20product%20of%20unlawful%20encroachment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHistorical%20Backdrop%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20property%20dispute%20can%20be%20traced%20back%20to%201918%20when%20the%20land%20was%20first%20occupied%20by%20Rustam%20Ali%20Khan%2C%20the%20father%20of%20Liaquat%20Ali%20Khan.%20Liaquat%20Ali%20Khan%20was%20born%20in%20Haryana's%20Karnal%20and%20was%20the%20second%20son%20of%20Rustam%20Ali%20Khan%20and%20his%20wife%20Mahmoodah%20Begum%2C%20the%20daughter%20of%20Nawab%20Quaher%20Ali%20Khan%20UP's%20Saharanpur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20a%20deep%20connection%20with%20Muzaffarnagar%2C%20where%20he%20campaigned%20successfully%20for%20the%20United%20Provinces%20Legislative%20Council%20in%201926.%20His%20association%20with%20the%20region%20was%20not%20just%20political%20but%20also%20familial%2C%20as%20his%20extended%20family%20lived%20in%20the%20area%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201932%2C%20Liaquat%20Ali%20Khan%20was%20elected%20Deputy%20President%20of%20the%20United%20Provinces%20Legislative%20Council%20and%20continued%20his%20political%20career%20until%20his%20elevation%20to%20the%20Central%20Legislative%20Assembly%20in%201940.%20The%20Khan%20family's%20political%20influence%20in%20the%20region%20was%20substantial%2C%20and%20their%20holdings%20in%20Muzaffarnagar%20were%20significant%2C%20spanning%20several%20properties%2C%20including%20the%20one%20in%20question.%20However%2C%20after%20the%20Partition%20of%20India%20in%201947%2C%20the%20fate%20of%20these%20properties%20changed%20dramatically.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Liaquat%20Ali%20Khan%20with%20his%20wife%20and%20children%2C%20June%2C%201947.%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Liaquat%20Ali%20Khan%20with%20his%20wife%20and%20children%2C%20June%2C%201947.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fcuq492fg_liaquat-ali-khan-_625x300_07_December_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELiaquat%20Ali%20Khan%20with%20his%20wife%20and%20children%2C%20June%2C%201947.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Getty%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELiaquat%20Ali%20Khan's%20migration%20to%20Pakistan%20turned%20his%20Indian%20properties%20into%20%26quot%3Benemy%20properties%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20designation%20under%20Indian%20law%20that%20applies%20to%20the%20assets%20of%20individuals%20who%20left%20the%20country%20for%20Pakistan%20after%20the%20Partition.%20In%20the%20years%20following%20his%20migration%2C%20his%20family's%20assets%20in%20India%20became%20a%20point%20of%20contention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELiaquat%20Ali%20Khan%20was%20shot%20twice%20in%20the%20chest%20while%20addressing%20a%20100%2C000-strong%20rally%20in%20Rawalpindi%20in%201951.%20His%20assassin%2C%20Said%20Akbar%20Khan%2C%20was%20fatally%20shot%20by%20Pakistani%20security%20forces%20seconds%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Mosque%20And%20Shops%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20controversy%20surrounding%20the%20land%20escalated%20when%20a%20mosque%20was%20constructed%20on%20the%20property%20in%20question%2C%20situated%20directly%20across%20from%20the%20Muzaffarnagar%20railway%20station.%20Sanjay%20Arora%2C%20the%20convener%20of%20a%20group%20called%20the%20Rashtriya%20Hindu%20Shakti%20Sangathan%2C%20brought%20attention%20to%20the%20construction%20in%202023%2C%20alleging%20that%20the%20mosque%20and%20shops%20were%20built%20illegally%20on%20enemy%20property.%20Mr%20Arora%20argued%20that%20the%20mosque%2C%20which%20he%20claimed%20was%20%26quot%3Bconstructed%20like%20a%20hotel%26quot%3B%2C%20did%20not%20adhere%20to%20the%20legal%20regulations%20governing%20construction%20in%20the%20area%2C%20as%20it%20had%20not%20received%20approval%20from%20the%20Muzaffarnagar%20Development%20Authority%20(MDA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20no%20documents%20for%20this%20property%20with%20the%20Waqf%20Board%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Arora%20claimed.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20an%20individual%20has%20moved%20to%20Pakistan%2C%20their%20land%20is%20either%20illegal%20property%20or%20enemy%20property.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20mosque%20and%20the%20shops%20in%20queston.%20%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22The%20mosque%20and%20the%20shops%20in%20queston.%20%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fl6ojfci_liaquat-ali-khan-mosque-and-four-shops-_625x300_07_December_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mosque%20and%20the%20shops%20in%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Arora%2C%20without%20providing%20any%20evidence%20to%20back%20his%20claim%2C%20made%20further%20allegations%20that%20the%20property%20and%20the%20mosque%20that%20it%20hosts%20are%20a%20%26quot%3Bthreat%20to%20national%20security%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20complaint%20to%20the%20district%20administration%20led%20to%20a%20multi-tiered%20investigation%20by%20local%20authorities%2C%20which%20included%20representatives%20from%20the%20Muzaffarnagar%20District%20Magistrate's%20Office%2C%20the%20Revenue%20Department%2C%20and%20the%20Municipal%20Corporation.%20The%20investigation%20was%20escalated%20when%20it%20was%20referred%20to%20the%20Enemy%20Property%20Office%20in%20Delhi%2C%20where%20a%20team%20was%20dispatched%20to%20survey%20the%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Sanjay%20Arora%2C%20the%20convener%20of%20the%20Rashtriya%20Hindu%20Shakti%20Sangathan.%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Sanjay%20Arora%2C%20the%20convener%20of%20the%20Rashtriya%20Hindu%20Shakti%20Sangathan.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2F9o4g2g9o_sanjay-arora-the-convener-of-a-group-called-the-rashtriya-hindu-shakti-sangathan_625x300_07_December_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESanjay%20Arora%2C%20the%20convener%20of%20the%20Rashtriya%20Hindu%20Shakti%20Sangathan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20exact%20worth%20of%20the%20property%20has%20not%20been%20calculated%20yet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Enemy%20Property%20Act%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Enemy%20Property%20Act%2C%201968%2C%20governs%20the%20appropriation%20of%20properties%20in%20India%20belonging%20to%20Pakistani%20nationals.%20Introduced%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20India-Pakistan%20War%20of%201965%2C%20the%20Act%20transfers%20ownership%20of%20such%20properties%20to%20the%20Custodian%20of%20Enemy%20Property%20for%20India%2C%20a%20designated%20government%20authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Enemy%20Property%20Agency%2C%20the%20land%20in%20question%20had%20indeed%20been%20declared%20enemy%20property.%20The%20property%20was%20found%20to%20be%20under%20the%20ownership%20of%20Rustam%20Ali%20Khan%2C%20Liaquat%20Ali%20Khan's%20father%2C%20who%20had%20left%20India%20for%20Pakistan%20after%20the%20Partition.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20these%20findings%2C%20the%20government%20moved%20to%20issue%20a%20legal%20notice%20to%20the%20occupants%20of%20the%20land%2C%20directing%20them%20to%20vacate%20the%20premises.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Counter-Claim%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20declaration%20of%20the%20land%20as%20enemy%20property%2C%20there%20remains%20a%20counter-narrative.%20Those%20occupying%20the%20mosque%20and%20the%20shops%20argue%20that%20the%20land%20was%20legally%20waqf%20(a%20form%20of%20Islamic%20endowment)%2C%20which%20means%20it%20was%20donated%20for%20religious%20purposes.%20According%20to%20the%20individuals%20on%20the%20Muslim%20side%20of%20the%20dispute%2C%20the%20property%20had%20been%20registered%20with%20the%20Waqf%20Board%2C%20and%20they%20have%20submitted%20documentation%20to%20that%20effect%2C%20including%20a%20letter%20from%201937%20to%20bolster%20their%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20key%20figures%20defending%20the%20status%20of%20the%20property%20as%20waqf%20is%20Mohammad%20Athar%2C%20a%20local%20businessman%20who%20runs%20a%20shop%20on%20the%20land.%20He%20insists%20that%20the%20property%20belonged%20to%20Rustam%20Ali%20Khan%2C%20who%20had%20endowed%20it%20to%20the%20Waqf.%20Mr%20Athar%20dismissed%20the%20claim%20that%20the%20land%20belongs%20to%20Liaquat%20Ali%20Khan%20and%20claimed%20that%20political%20motivations%20and%20misinformation%20are%20driving%20the%20entire%20dispute.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Mohammad%20Athar%2C%20a%20local%20businessman%20who%20runs%20a%20shop%20on%20the%20land.%20%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Mohammad%20Athar%2C%20a%20local%20businessman%20who%20runs%20a%20shop%20on%20the%20land.%20%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2F468ab03o_mohammad-athar-a-local-businessman-who-runs-a-shop-on-the-land-_625x300_07_December_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMohammad%20Athar%2C%20a%20local%20businessman%20who%20runs%20a%20shop%20on%20the%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20land%20did%20not%20belong%20to%20Liaquat%20Ali%20Khan%20but%20his%20father%20Rustam%20Ali%20Khan%20who%20donated%20the%20land%20to%20waqf%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Athar%20claimed.%20%26quot%3BThe%20mosque%20at%20this%20property%20has%20existed%20before%20the%20partition%20of%20the%20country.%20We%20have%20presented%20all%20the%20evidence%20to%20prove%20this%2C%20and%20we%20hope%20the%20government%20rethinks%20its%20decision%20and%20deliberates%20on%20the%20matter%20once%20again%20as%20the%20livelihoods%20of%20several%20families%20depend%20on%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20claimants%20argue%20that%20the%20mosque%2C%20which%20has%20existed%20for%20decades%2C%20was%20not%20built%20in%20violation%20of%20any%20law%20and%20that%20the%20rent%20collected%20from%20the%20shops%20is%20legitimate.%20They%20maintain%20that%20the%20designation%20of%20the%20land%20as%20enemy%20property%20is%20an%20incorrect%20claim%20based%20on%20misinterpretation%20of%20historical%20records.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELegal%20Ramifications%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20legal%20complexities%20surrounding%20the%20ownership%20of%20enemy%20property%20are%20not%20unique%20to%20Muzaffarnagar.%20Across%20India%2C%20several%20properties%20previously%20owned%20by%20individuals%20who%20migrated%20to%20Pakistan%20after%20the%20Partition%20have%20been%20caught%20in%20similar%20disputes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20landmark%20case%2C%20the%20Indian%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20in%202005%20that%20the%20property%20of%20Mohammed%20Amir%20Mohammed%20Khan%2C%20the%20erstwhile%20Raja%20of%20UP's%20Mehmoodabad%2C%20was%20classified%20as%20enemy%