0a%20joint%20effort%20to%20grow%20the%20overall%20size%20of%20the%20market.%20The%20customer%20profiles%20and%20AI%20workloads%20they%20target%20are%20also%20different.%20He%20added%20that%20Nvidia's%20GPUs%20would%20remain%20dominant%20for%20the%20foreseeable%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20interview%2C%20Hutt%20discussed%20AWS's%20partnership%20with%20Anthropic%2C%20which%20is%20set%20to%20be%20Project%20Rainer's%20first%20customer.%20The%20two%20companies%20have%20worked%20closely%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-tries-again-anthropic-ai-chips-trainium-nvidia-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20recently%20invested%20an%20additional%20%244%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20AI%20startup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20shared%20his%20thoughts%20on%20AWS's%20partnership%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintels-new-leaders-address-outgoing-ceo-pat-gelsingers-internal-meeting-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIntel%2C%20whose%20CEO%2C%20Pat%20Gelsinger%2C%20just%20retired%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20said%20AWS%20would%20continue%20to%20work%20with%20the%20struggling%20chip%20giant%20because%20customer%20demand%20for%20Intel's%20server%20chips%20remained%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%20AWS%20said%20it%20was%20considering%20selling%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-not-enough-demand-amd-ai-chips-aws-nvidia-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAMD's%20new%20AI%20chips%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20Hutt%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esaid%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethose%20chips%20still%20weren't%20available%20on%20AWS%20because%20customers%20hadn't%20shown%20strong%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20Q%26amp%3BA%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20clarity%20and%20length.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20have%20been%20a%20lot%20of%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-tries-again-anthropic-ai-chips-trainium-nvidia-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Eheadlines%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20saying%20Amazon%20is%20out%20to%20get%20Nvidia%20with%20its%20new%20AI%20chips.%20Can%20you%20talk%20about%20that%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20usually%20look%20at%20these%20headlines%2C%20and%20I%20giggle%20a%20bit%20because%2C%20really%2C%20it's%20not%20about%20unseating%20Nvidia.%20Nvidia%20is%20a%20very%20important%20partner%20for%20us.%20It's%20really%20about%20giving%20customers%20choices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20ahead%20of%20us%20to%20ensure%20that%20we%20continuously%20give%20more%20customers%20the%20ability%20to%20use%20these%20chips.%20And%20Nvidia%20is%20not%20going%20anywhere.%20They%20have%20a%20good%20solution%20and%20a%20solid%20road%20map.%20We%20just%20announced%20the%20P6%20instances%20%5BAWS%20servers%20with%20Nvidia's%20latest%20Blackwell%20GPUs%5D%2C%20so%20there's%20a%20continuous%20investment%20in%20the%20Nvidia%20product%20line%20as%20well.%20It's%20really%20to%20give%20customers%20options.%20Nothing%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENvidia%20is%20a%20great%20supplier%20of%20AWS%2C%20and%20our%20customers%20love%20Nvidia.%20I%20would%20not%20discount%20Nvidia%20in%20any%20way%2C%20shape%2C%20or%20form.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20you%20want%20to%20see%20Nvidia's%20use%20case%20increase%20on%20AWS%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20customers%20believe%20that's%20the%20way%20they%20need%20to%20go%2C%20then%20they'll%20do%20it.%20Of%20course%2C%20if%20it's%20good%20for%20customers%2C%20it's%20good%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20market%20is%20very%20big%2C%20so%20there's%20room%20for%20multiple%20vendors%20here.%20We're%20not%20forcing%20anybody%20to%20use%20those%20chips%2C%20but%20we're%20working%20very%20hard%20to%20ensure%20that%20our%20major%20tenets%2C%20which%20are%20high%20performance%20and%20lower%20cost%2C%20will%20materialize%20to%20benefit%20our%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDoes%20it%20mean%20AWS%20is%20OK%20being%20in%20second%20place%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20a%20competition.%20There's%20no%20machine-learning%20award%20ceremony%20every%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20a%20customer%20like%20Anthropic%2C%20there's%20very%20clear%20scientific%20evidence%20that%20larger%20compute%20infrastructure%20allows%20you%20to%20build%20larger%20models%20with%20more%20data.%20And%20if%20you%20do%20that%2C%20you%20get%20higher%20accuracy%20and%20more%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20ability%20to%20scale%20capacity%20to%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20Trainium%202%20chips%20gives%20them%20the%20opportunity%20to%20innovate%20on%20something%20they%20couldn't%20have%20done%20before.%20They%20get%20a%205x%20boost%20in%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20being%20No.%201%20important%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20market%20is%20big%20enough.%20No.%202%20is%20a%20very%20good%20position%20to%20be%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20saying%20I'm%20No.%202%20or%20No.%201%2C%20by%20the%20way.%20But%20it's%20really%20not%20something%20I'm%20even%20thinking%20about.%20We're%20so%20early%20in%20our%20journey%20here%20in%20machine%20learning%20in%20general%2C%20the%20industry%20in%20general%2C%20and%20also%20on%20the%20chips%20specifically%2C%20we're%20just%20heads%20down%20serving%20customers%20like%20Anthropic%2C%20Apple%2C%20and%20all%20the%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20not%20even%20doing%20competitive%20analysis%20with%20Nvidia.%20I'm%20not%20running%20benchmarks%20against%20Nvidia.%20I%20don't%20need%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20there's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmlcommons.org%2Fbenchmarks%2Ftraining%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMLPerf%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20industry%20performance%20benchmark.%20Companies%20that%20participate%20in%20MLPerf%20have%20performance%20engineers%20working%20just%20to%20improve%20MLPerf%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20completely%20a%20distraction%20for%20us.%20We're%20not%20participating%20in%20that%20because%20we%20don't%20want%20to%20waste%20time%20on%20a%20benchmark%20that%20isn't%20customer-focused.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20the%20surface%2C%20it%20seems%20like%20helping%20companies%20grow%20on%20AWS%20isn't%20always%20beneficial%20for%20AWS's%20own%20products%20because%20you're%20competing%20with%20them.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20the%20same%20company%20that%20is%20the%20best%20place%20Netflix%20is%20running%20on%2C%20and%20we%20also%20have%20Prime%20Video.%20It's%20part%20of%20our%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20will%20say%20that%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20customers%20that%20are%20still%20on%20GPUs.%20A%20lot%20of%20customers%20love%20GPUs%2C%20and%20they%20have%20no%20intention%20to%20move%20to%20Trainium%20anytime%20soon.%20And%20that's%20fine%2C%20because%2C%20again%2C%20we're%20giving%20them%20the%20options%20and%20they%20decide%20what%20they%20want%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20you%20see%20these%20AI%20tools%20becoming%20more%20commoditized%20in%20the%20future%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20really%20hope%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20started%20this%20in%202016%2C%20the%20problem%20was%20that%20there%20was%20no%20operating%20system%20for%20machine%20learning.%20So%20we%20really%20had%20to%20invent%20all%20the%20tools%20that%20go%20around%20these%20chips%20to%20make%20them%20work%20for%20our%20customers%20as%20seamlessly%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20machine%20learning%20becomes%20commoditized%20on%20the%20software%20and%20hardware%20sides%2C%20it's%20a%20good%20thing%20for%20everybody.%20It%20means%20that%20it's%20easier%20to%20use%20those%20solutions.%20But%20running%20machine%20learning%20meaningfully%20is%20still%20an%20art.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20some%20of%20the%20different%20types%20of%20workloads%20customers%20might%20want%20to%20run%20on%20GPUs%20versus%20Trainium%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGPUs%20are%20more%20of%20a%20general-purpose%20processor%20of%20machine%20learning.%20All%20the%20researchers%20and%20data%20scientists%20in%20the%20world%20know%20how%20to%20use%20Nvidia%20pretty%20well.%20If%20you%20invent%20something%20new%2C%20if%20you%20do%20that%20on%20GPU%2C%20then%20things%20will%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20invent%20something%20new%20on%20specialized%20chips%2C%20you'll%20have%20to%20either%20ensure%20compiler%20technology%20understands%20what%20you%20just%20built%20or%20create%20your%20own%20compute%20kernel%20for%20that%20workload.%20We're%20focused%20mainly%20on%20use%20cases%20where%20our%20customers%20tell%20us%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20this%20is%20what%20we%20need.%26quot%3B%20Usually%20the%20customers%20we%20get%20are%20the%20ones%20that%20are%20seeing%20increased%20costs%20as%20an%20issue%20and%20are%20trying%20to%20look%20for%20alternatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20the%20most%20advanced%20workloads%20are%20usually%20reserved%20for%20Nvidia%20chips%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsually.%20If%20data-science%20folks%20need%20to%20continuously%20run%20experiments%2C%20they'll%20probably%20do%20that%20on%20a%20GPU%20cluster.%20When%20they%20know%20what%20they%20want%20to%20do%2C%20that's%20where%20they%20have%20more%20options.%20That's%20where%20Trainium%20really%20shines%2C%20because%20it%20gives%20high%20performance%20at%20a%20lower%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAWS%20CEO%20Matt%20Garman%20previously%20said%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20workloads%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20on%20Nvidia.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20makes%20sense.%20We%20give%20value%20to%20customers%20who%20have%20a%20large%20spend%20and%20are%20trying%20to%20see%20how%20they%20can%20control%20the%20costs%20a%20bit%20better.%20When%20Matt%20says%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20workloads%2C%20it%20means%20medical%20imaging%2C%20speech%20recognition%2C%20weather%20forecasting%2C%20and%20all%20sorts%20of%20workloads%20that%20we're%20not%20really%20focused%20on%20right%20now%20because%20we%20have%20large%20customers%20who%20ask%20us%20to%20do%20bigger%20things.%20So%20that%20statement%20is%20100%25%20correct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20nutshell%2C%20we%20want%20to%20continue%20to%20be%20the%20best%20place%20for%20GPUs%20and%2C%20of%20course%2C%20Trainium%20when%20customers%20need%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20has%20Anthropic%20done%20to%20help%20AWS%20in%20the%20AI%20space%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20have%20very%20strong%20opinions%20of%20what%20they%20need%2C%20and%20they%20come%20back%20to%20us%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20can%20we%20add%20feature%20A%20to%20your%20future%20chip%3F%26quot%3B%20It's%20a%20dialogue.%20Some%20ideas%20they%20came%20up%20with%20weren't%20feasible%20to%20even%20implement%20in%20a%20piece%20of%20silicon.%20We%20actually%20implemented%20some%20ideas%2C%20and%20for%20others%20we%20came%20back%20with%20a%20better%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20they're%20such%20experts%20in%20building%20foundation%20models%2C%20this%20really%20helps%20us%20home%20in%20on%20building%20chips%20that%20are%20really%20good%20at%20what%20they%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20just%20announced%20Project%20Rainier%20together.%20This%20is%20someone%20who%20wants%20to%20use%20a%20lot%20of%20those%20chips%20as%20fast%20as%20possible.%20It's%20not%20an%20idea%20%E2%80%94%20we're%20actually%20building%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20you%20talk%20about%20Intel%3F%20AWS's%20Graviton%20chips%20are%20replacing%20a%20lot%20of%20Intel%20chips%20at%20AWS%20data%20centers.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20correct%20you%20here.%20Graviton%20is%20not%20replacing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-analysts-technologies-foundry-ai-x86-chips-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ex86%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20not%20like%20we're%20yanking%20out%20x86%20and%20putting%20Graviton%20in%20place.%20But%20again%2C%20following%20customer%20demand%2C%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20our%20recent%20landings%20on%20CPUs%20were%20Graviton.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20means%20that%20the%20customer%20demand%20for%20Graviton%20is%20growing.%20But%20we're%20still%20selling%20a%20lot%20of%20x86%20cores%20too%20for%20our%20customers%2C%20and%20we%20think%20we're%20the%20best%20place%20to%20do%20that.%20We're%20not%20competing%20with%20these%20companies%2C%20but%20we're%20treating%20them%20as%20good%20suppliers%2C%20and%20we%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20business%20to%20do%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20important%20is%20Intel%20going%20forward%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20will%20for%20sure%20continue%20to%20be%20a%20great%20partner%20for%20AWS.%20There%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20use%20cases%20that%20run%20really%20well%20on%20Intel%20cores.%20We're%20still%20deploying%20them.%20There's%20no%20intention%20to%20stop.%20It's%20really%20following%20customer%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20AWS%20still%20considering%20selling%20AMD's%20AI%20chips%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAMD%20is%20a%20great%20partner%20for%20AWS.%20We%20sell%20a%20lot%20of%20AMD%20CPUs%20to%20customers%20as%20instances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20machine-learning%20product%20line%20is%20always%20under%20consideration.%20If%20customers%20strongly%20indicate%20that%20they%20need%20it%2C%20then%20there's%20no%20reason%20not%20to%20deploy%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20you're%20not%20seeing%20that%20yet%20for%20AMD's%20AI%20chips%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20supportive%20are%20Amazon%20CEO%20Andy%20Jassy%20and%20Garman%20of%20the%20AI%20chip%20business%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20very%20supportive.%20We%20meet%20them%20on%20a%20regular%20basis.%20There's%20a%20lot%20of%20focus%20across%20leadership%20in%20the%20company%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20the%20customers%20who%20need%20ML%20solutions%20get%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETher