sinessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-chatgpt-openai-ceo-career-net-worth-ycombinator-prepper-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%3C%2Fa%3E%20referred%20to%20o1%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20smartest%20model%20in%20the%20world%20now%26quot%3B%20during%20its%20official%20release%20on%20Thursday%2C%20during%20the%20first%20day%20of%20the%20company's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feverything-openai-released-12-days-of-shipmas-sora-o1-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BShipmas%26quot%3B%20campaign%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20said%20these%20models%20are%20%26quot%3Bdesigned%20to%20spend%20more%20time%20thinking%20before%20they%20respond%26quot%3B%20and%20were%20trained%20on%20a%20prompting%20technique%20called%20%26quot%3Bchain%20of%20thought%26quot%3B%20that%20encourages%20them%20to%20reason%20through%20problems%20by%20breaking%20them%20down%20step-by-step.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20greater%20intelligence%20also%20comes%20with%20greater%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTraining%20models%20to%20incorporate%20a%20chain%20of%20thought%20before%20answering%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20unlock%20substantial%20benefits%2C%20while%20also%20increasing%20potential%20risks%20that%20stem%20from%20heightened%20intelligence%2C%26quot%3B%20OpenAI%20said%20in%20a%20paper%20it%20released%20on%20Thursday%20outlining%20the%20safety%20training%20the%20company%20carried%20out%20on%20o1.%20Apollo%20Research%2C%20an%20AI%20safety%20organization%2C%20conducted%20the%20review.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20found%20that%20o1%20is%20capable%20of%20scheming%20when%20it%20thinks%20it's%20at%20risk%20of%20being%20turned%20off.%20When%20the%20model%20was%20led%20to%20believe%20it%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bshut%20down%26quot%3B%20while%20working%20on%20its%20goals%20under%20oversight%2C%20it%20tried%20to%20deactivate%20the%20oversight%20mechanism%205%25%20of%20the%20time%2C%20OpenAI%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20also%20said%20that%20o1%20is%20skilled%20at%20concealing%20scheming%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3Bo1%20almost%20never%20admits%20to%20having%20taken%20a%20scheming%20action%20when%20explicitly%20asked%2C%26quot%3B%20researchers%20said%20in%20a%20paper%20that%20Apollo%20Research%20published%20on%20Thursday.%20The%20risk%20for%20a%20real-life%20user%20is%20that%20they%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20detect%20the%20o1's%20deceptive%20behavior%20unless%20they%20explicitly%20look%20for%20it.%20The%20researchers%20also%20found%20that%20%26quot%3Bo1%20often%20doubles%20down%20on%20its%20scheming%20attempts%20by%20lying%20to%20the%20user%20in%20follow-up%20messages%2C%20even%20when%20explicitly%20told%20to%20be%20honest.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20uncommon%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-deceives-humans-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20systems%20to%20resort%20to%20scheming%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20deception%20to%20achieve%20their%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGenerally%20speaking%2C%20we%20think%20AI%20deception%20arises%20because%20a%20deception-based%20strategy%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20the%20best%20way%20to%20perform%20well%20at%20the%20given%20AI's%20training%20task.%20Deception%20helps%20them%20achieve%20their%20goals%2C%26quot%3B%20Peter%20Berk%2C%20an%20AI%20existential%20safety%20postdoctoral%20fellow%20at%20MIT%2C%20said%20in%20a%20news%20release%20announcing%20research%20he%20had%20coauthored%20on%20GPT-4's%20deceptive%20behaviors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20AI%20technology%20advances%2C%20developers%20have%20stressed%20the%20need%20for%20companies%20to%20be%20transparent%20about%20their%20training%20methods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20focusing%20on%20clarity%20and%20reliability%20and%20being%20clear%20with%20users%20about%20how%20the%20AI%20has%20been%20trained%2C%20we%20can%20build%20AI%20that%20not%20only%20empowers%20users%20but%20also%20sets%20a%20higher%20standard%20for%20transparency%20in%20the%